  ### How prompting in Lyria 3 works
  
  [Try in Gemini](https://gemini.google.com/music?utm_source=deepmind.google&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=gdm&utm_content=)
  
  ![A digital graphic with a vibrant yellow and white gradient background. A translucent card in the center contains text labeled "Prompt" which reads: "A massive, anthemic rock song with an emotive male singer."](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/VeEbO2nr9oQCx_GPZr8R7lpTQfeOOIBU3NQTR25iwvPvrhrRqiU9BIHOGnrLX05dPscC7-f9DNLJex6qButOHGBapJhSOlAtNUJH87-5DXvmTOVJ8eI=w1440-h1920-n-nu)
  
  ### Simple prompts
  
  Get started with something basic. Request “a rock song” with a chosen lyrical theme and vocal style. Lyria 3 will generate a track with instruments and vocals.
  
  ![A digital graphic with a soft blue and lavender gradient background. A translucent card in the center contains text labeled "Prompt" which reads: "Create a track that reimagines the ideas in this image."](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/Ccmn3P7JS9VUqD7RsSHiGd37-BoGrl_70tTZrkiyzM3OhN4jKXMEOQrUSVCJV9XnL_e6SXRNJSfP3pPZ5HPD8KWbyhf6WDpiwPDCR2iJye_jay27-5E=w1440-h1920-n-nu)
  
  ### Image-to-music prompts
  
  Upload an image to generate music to match. Try uploading holiday snaps, photos of your dog – or add a musical dimension to your visual art.
  
  ![A digital graphic with a soft green gradient background. A translucent card in the center contains text labeled "Prompt" which reads: "An intimate, sophisticated Brazilian Bossa Nova track evoking the quiet atmosphere of a Rio beach at sunset. The tempo is a gentle." The text below this is artistically blurred, suggesting a deep, technical description of musical layers.](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/0emBaarAftoPTTpUjlsmcdg6pxQCLsMSgrZLcDnVxYP0ced6D_XW9rDjUUl7Qdwo9uik_XEzIGsjaWFEWSIBfaWl_GipxEHI-HI1VEsdpi27Jwo9Jw=w1440-h1920-n-nu)
  
  ### Detailed, structured prompts
  
  Think about the tempo, dynamics, and instruments you want in your track. The more detail you add, the more control you have over the music.
  
  - [Prompt construction](https://deepmind.google/models/lyria/prompt-guide/#prompt-construction)
  - [Prompting with images](https://deepmind.google/models/lyria/prompt-guide/#prompting-with-images)
  - [Prompting vocals and lyrics](https://deepmind.google/models/lyria/prompt-guide/#prompting-vocals-and-lyrics)
  - [Experimenting with prompts](https://deepmind.google/models/lyria/prompt-guide/#experimenting-with-prompts)
  
  ### What to think about while creating prompts
  
  #### Think about your genre, tempo, and the instruments you want to hear. Experiment by adding details to shape the mood and dynamics.
  
  Genre – or a mix of genres
  
  Pick a genre and era, like early 90s hip-hop, or 2000s pop. Or blend different genres within one song. Do you want a catchy K-pop tune with a Motown edge? Or merge classical violins into a funk track? It’s up to you.
  
  Tempo
  
  Ask for a fast or slow song. Or set a rough tempo by asking for a certain type of music – like a slow ballad, modern pop, or drum and bass.
  
  Instruments
  
  Add unexpected instruments into your chosen genre. “1950s jazz” will likely feature saxophones and trumpets. But you can add other instruments—like an 80s synth—to round out your sound. Or, if you don’t specify instruments, Lyria will automatically choose instruments to suit the genre.
  
  Dynamics
  
  Think about how music flows between sections. Maybe a quiet piano builds into an explosive chorus. Perhaps there’s an instrumental section. Or the vocals might get calmer and quieter as the track progresses.
  
