  ## General summary
  
  The Gemini app now lets you create custom music using Google DeepMind’s Lyria 3. Just describe an idea or upload a photo, and Gemini will generate a 30-second track with custom cover art. Also, all tracks generated in the Gemini app are embedded with SynthID, our imperceptible watermark for identifying Google AI-generated content.
  
  Summaries were generated by Google AI. Generative AI is experimental.
  
  
  ## Bullet points
  
  - Gemini's new feature, using Lyria 3, lets you create custom music from text or images.
  - Just describe your idea, and Gemini will generate a 30-second track with custom cover art.
  - Lyria 3 improves on previous models with lyrics, creative control, and complex tracks.
  - SynthID watermarks all Gemini-generated music, and you can verify if audio is AI-made.
  - Available in the Gemini app for users 18+ in multiple languages, with higher limits for subscribers.
  
  Summaries were generated by Google AI. Generative AI is experimental.
  
  
  ## Basic explainer
  
  The Gemini app can now make music using Google's new AI model, Lyria 3. You can type in a description or upload a photo, and Gemini will create a short song based on it. The AI adds a special code to the music, so people know it was made by AI. This new feature is supposed to help people express themselves in a fun way.
  
